The paper deals with the design of proximity data structures, which is a central topic in computer science. The use of Ramsey partitions is a technique that is commonly used in computational geometry and combinatorics, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a likely category. The paper also deals with metric embeddings, which is a topic in both cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MG (Machine Learning). The use of approximation algorithms and the analysis of query time suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories.
